		h1 How to install?
		p.container
			| To install it you need only some dependencies and the sources files.
		h2 What dependencies need?
		p.container 
			| Something important is that Chico depends on jQuery to work. Besides that, you can add some snippets to improve the cross-browser task. Also, you can add PNG fix for non transparent png images in old browsers. 
		h3 Conditional comments
		p.container	
			| We hate writting CSS hacks. Instead of hacking the code, we rather use
			a(href='/how-to/browser-sniffing') IE's conditional comments
			|  so if you paste this code in your HTML, Chico-UI will know how to fix the visual inconsistencies
		.snippet
			p Snippet
			div	
				pre.code
					|<!doctype html>
					|<!--[if IE]><![endif]--><!--[if lt IE 7 ]> <html lang="es" class="no-js ie6"> <![endif]--> 
					|<!--[if IE 7 ]><html lang="es" class="no-js ie7"> <![endif]-->
					|<!--[if IE 8 ]><html lang="es" class="no-js ie8"> <![endif]--> 
					|<!--[if IE 9 ]><html lang="es" class="no-js ie9"> <![endif]-->
					|<!--[if (gt IE 9)|!(IE)]><!--> <html lang="es" class="no-js"> <!--<![endif]-->	
		h3 jQuery JavaScript Library
		p.container	
			| Most of this frameworkâ€™s functionality is built on 
			a(href='http://www.jquery.com') JQuery
			|  , that's why we need to pre-load this tool.
		.snippet
			p Snippet
			div
				pre.code
					|<head>
					|	<title>Your title</title>
					|	<script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.x.x/jquery.min.js"></script>
					|	...
		h3 DD_belatedPNG
		p.container	
			| The 
			a(href='http://www.dillerdesign.com/experiment/DD_belatedPNG',title='PNG Support for old browsers.') DD_belatedPNG
			|  solution is for .png transparencies in browsers that don't support this feature. We fix it with another conditional comment
		.snippet
			p Snippet
			div
				pre.code
					|	...
					|	<!--[if lt IE 7 ]><script src="./libs/js/dd_belatedpng.js"></script>
					|	<script> DD_belatedPNG.fix('img, .ico'); //fix any <img> or .ico background-images </script>
					|	<![endif]-->
					|	...
		h2 Which are the sources?
		p.container
			| You only add the CSS and JavaScript sources, and that's all! 
			br
			| Make sure to add the Styles on the 
			code &lt;head&gt;
			| .
			
